content.text:
## Spike 4 evidence (concurrent dev:full, MFE 100%, end-to-end)

**Setup**: portless daemon on `:1355`, two real git worktrees (primary + sibling on branch `fix-ui`), each running fake `lightfast-app` + `lightfast-www` wrapped in `portless run`, plus an MFE proxy wrapped in `portless run --name lightfast`. Both MFE proxies read their own per-worktree config generated from the same committed `microfrontends.json` template.

**Result — perfect routing isolation:**

```
curl https://lightfast.localhost:1355/sign-in       → primary-app (port 4051)
curl https://lightfast.localhost:1355/docs/intro    → primary-www (port 4899)
curl https://fix-ui.lightfast.localhost:1355/sign-in    → sibling-app (port 4301)
curl https://fix-ui.lightfast.localhost:1355/docs/intro → sibling-www (port 4761)
```

## What made it work — and the answer to "do we need a script?"

Two new findings from this spike:

1. **`portless get <name>` is worktree-aware** (verified: from primary returns `https://lightfast-app.localhost:1355`; from sibling returns `https://fix-ui.lightfast-app.localhost:1355`). This is the Vercel/portless-shipped primitive for "what's this service's URL in the *current* worktree?" — eliminates all the offset-hashing math from my earlier proposal.

2. **`MFE_CONFIG` env var (inline JSON) does NOT work for `microfrontends proxy`.** I was wrong earlier. `MFE_CONFIG` is read only by the runtime middleware (`MicrofrontendsServer.fromEnv` at `cli.cjs:1812`). The `proxy` CLI command at `cli.cjs:3104` calls `LocalProxy.fromFile` → `infer()`, which reads `VC_MICROFRONTENDS_CONFIG` (file path), never `MFE_CONFIG`. **A file must be written.**

Combined: there's **no escape** from writing a per-worktree config file. The MFE CLI's design requires it. But the file-writing logic is now tiny because `portless get` does the worktree-aware URL math:

```js
// 10 lines. Lives at apps/app/scripts/mfe-config.cjs (or inlined in package.json).
const {execSync}=require('child_process');
const fs=require('fs');
const c=JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync('./microfrontends.json','utf8'));
for (const name of Object.keys(c.applications)) {
  const url=execSync(`portless get ${name}`).toString().trim();
  if (c.applications[name].development) c.applications[name].development.local=url;
}
const out=`/tmp/mfe-${process.cwd().replace(/\W/g,'-')}.json`;
fs.writeFileSync(out, JSON.stringify(c));
process.stdout.write(out);
```

Used as:
```jsonc
"proxy": "VC_MICROFRONTENDS_CONFIG=$(node ./scripts/mfe-config.cjs) portless run --name lightfast bash -c 'export MFE_LOCAL_PROXY_PORT=$PORT; exec microfrontends proxy --local-apps lightfast-app lightfast-www'"
```

Compared to the earlier proposal: no port-offset arithmetic, no `.gitignore` entry (config goes to `/tmp`), no hash-from-worktree-path. Just "ask portless for each app's URL, fill in `local`, point MFE at the result."

